Let $q$ be a real number with $|q| != 1$ and let $k$ be a positive integer.
Define a Laurent polynomial $f_k (X)$ in the variable $X$, depending on $q$ and
$k$, by


$ f_k (X) = product_(i=0)^(k-1) (1 - q^i X)(1 - q^(i+1) X^(-1)). $


Show that the constant term of $f_k (X)$, i.e., the coefficient of $X^0$ in
$f_k (X)$, is equal to


$ ((1 - q^(k+1))(1 - q^(k+2)) ... (1 - q^(2k)))/((1 - q)(1 - q^2) ... (1 - q^k)). $
